<li>Barak, Gregg (ed.). (1998). <i>Integrative criminology</i> (International Library of Criminology, Criminal Justice &amp; Penology.). Aldershot: Ashgate/Dartmouth. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1840140089" class="internal">ISBN 1-84014-008-9</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Philip_Pettit" title="Philip Pettit">Pettit, Philip</a> and <a href="/wiki/John_Braithwaite" title="John Braithwaite">Braithwaite, John</a>. <i>Not Just Deserts. A Republican Theory of Criminal Justice</i> ISBN13: 9780198240563 (see <a href="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0023-9216(1994)28%3A4%3C765%3ARCAVAC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-4" class="external text" title="http://links.jstor.org/sici?sici=0023-9216(1994)28%3A4%3C765%3ARCAVAC%3E2.0.CO%3B2-4" rel="nofollow">Republican Criminology and Victim Advocacy: Comment</a> for article concerning the book in <i><a href="/wiki/Law_%26_Society_Review" title="Law &amp; Society Review">Law &amp; Society Review</a></i>, Vol. 28, No. 4 (1995), pp. 765-776)</li>
</ul>
